* {{ill|Eiwa|ja|永和|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eiwa|1=Eiwa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11131293}} 1st year/{{ill|Tianshou|en|Tianshou|qid=Q10939676|lt=Tenshu|1=Tianshou}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1375|en|1375|qid=Q6277|lt=1375|1=1375}} {{ill|June 26|en|June 26|qid=Q2661|lt=June 26|1=June 26}}) – {{ill|Southern Court|ja|南朝|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Southern Court|qq=}} が {{ill|Bunchū|en|Bunchū|qid=Q1194181|lt=Bunchū|1=Bunchū}} より {{ill|Tianshou|en|Tianshou|qid=Q10939676|lt=Tenshu|1=Tianshou}} に {{ill|Era change|ja|改元|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Era change|1=era change|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11498853}}.
* {{ill|Kōka|en|Kōka|qid=Q1325317|lt=Kōka|1=Kōka}} 3rd year (閏5月) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1846|en|1846|qid=Q7640|lt=1846|1=1846}} {{ill|July 20|en|July 20|qid=Q2728|lt=July 20|1=July 20}}) – The American East India Squadron commander, Admiral {{ill|James Biddle|en|James Biddle|qid=Q3129637|lt=James Biddle|1=James Biddle}}, arrives in Uraga and requests trade. The shogunate refuses.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kenryaku|en|Kenryaku|qid=Q1194260|lt=Kenchō|1=Kenryaku}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1249|en|1249|qid=Q5485|lt=1249|1=1249}} {{ill|July 9|en|July 9|qid=Q2690|lt=July 9|1=July 9}}) – {{ill|Emperor Kameyama|en|Emperor Kameyama|qid=Q360972|lt=Kameyama Tennō|1=Emperor Kameyama}}, the 90th {{ill|Emperor of Japan|en|Emperor of Japan|qid=Q208233|lt=Emperor of Japan|1=Emperor of Japan}} (died {{ill|1305|en|1305|qid=Q5624|lt=1305|1=1305}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}} {{ill|July 16|en|July 16|qid=Q2731|lt=July 16|1=July 16}}) – {{ill|Hirose Takeo|en|Hirose Takeo|qid=Q711769|lt=Hirose Takeo|1=Hirose Takeo}}, a member of the {{ill|Navy|en|Navy|qid=Q4508|lt=Navy|1=Navy}} and a military personnel who became known as the first {{ill|Military Deity|ja|軍神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Military Deity|1=Military god|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11637440}} during the {{ill|Russo-Japanese War|en|Russo-Japanese War|qid=Q159950|lt=Russo-Japanese War|1=Russo-Japanese War}} (died {{ill|1904|en|1904|qid=Q2046|lt=1904|1=1904}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Bun'ei|en|Bun'ei|qid=Q1010103|lt=Bun'ei|1=Bun'ei}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1273|en|1273|qid=Q5526|lt=1273|1=1273}} {{ill|June 13|en|June 13|qid=Q2614|lt=June 13|1=June 13}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Masamura|en|Hōjō Masamura|qid=Q2408959|lt=Hōjō Masamura|1=Hōjō Masamura}}, the 7th {{ill|Shikken|en|Shikken|qid=Q1045904|lt=Shikken|1=Shikken}} of the {{ill|Kamakura shogunate|en|Kamakura shogunate|qid=Q736839|lt=Kamakura shogunate|1=Kamakura shogunate}} (born {{ill|1205|en|1205|qid=Q5229|lt=1205|1=1205}}).

